I have several study apps. This one seems to resembled the exam (which I passed using this app). This is how to use it: take the practice exam, if you know the answer - great! If you get it wrong OR guess, the app gives you the page # for the 6th Edition Firefighter Essentials book, look up the correct answer. Find the answer, highlight it, AND read the paragraph before and after the answer. Boom! You not only memorized the answer, you learned it too. Now go pass that exam.

I've found that the answers aren't always right. For example, one of the questions asked what osha's purpose is. The app has the answer "to ensure that the station is clean and well maintained". It give page 60 as the source of the question. The page definitely says that the answer is provide protection from hazards that could be fatal (not an exact quote of course. I have to wonder how many more are wrong. I can't really depends on this as a study guide. It's quite a shame.
It may be worth the money if you are struggling to pass.

Very helpful so far, ive read the entire book and taken every test. I feel very confident ill pass my state exam in a few days. I do have one question. ....I see the book has 21 chapters and this App has 24. Will a Florida State Exam cover just the book? Why does your App have 24?
replyContent: The app covers the extended version of the manual, which has 24 chapters.  The extra chapters cover Emergency Medical Care and HazMat, which is not included in all Firefighter I courses.  Requirements vary from state to state; some require separate training and certification; others include them in general firefighter certification.
